    {
      "id": "zQvo2eL5EWfr4PzDpcF1_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 300.9704284667969,
      "y": 839.888409641055,
      "width": 847.3192749023438,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 141164791,
      "version": 168,
      "versionNonce": 1006714682,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780380626228,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In LLMs, streaming means the model starts sending tokens (words) as soon \nas they’re generated, instead of waiting for the entire response \nto be ready before returning it.\n\nWhy Streaming?\n\n1. Faster response time - low drop-off rates\n2. Mimics human like conversation(Builds trust, feels alive and keeps the user engaged)\n3. Important for Multi-modal UIs\n4. Better UX for long output such as code\n5. You can cancel midway saving tokens\n6. You can interleave UI updates, e.g., show \"thinking...\", show tool results\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In LLMs, streaming means the model starts sending tokens (words) as soon \nas they’re generated, instead of waiting for the entire response \nto be ready before returning it.\n\nWhy Streaming?\n\n1. Faster response time - low drop-off rates\n2. Mimics human like conversation(Builds trust, feels alive and keeps the user engaged)\n3. Important for Multi-modal UIs\n4. Better UX for long output such as code\n5. You can cancel midway saving tokens\n6. You can interleave UI updates, e.g., show \"thinking...\", show tool results\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
